headline: Will West Coast Teamsters Strike Threat Reshape Sysco’s (SYY) Labor Cost Outlook?
summary: In the past week, more than 400 Sysco San Francisco workers represented by Teamsters voted unanimously to authorize a strike, demanding improved wages, benefits, and working conditions, with similar actions also taking place at Sysco Portland. This unified labor push, now encompassing nearly 800 workers across the West Coast, follows recent major Teamsters gains at competing food service providers and could pose significant operational risks for Sysco if collective agreements are not...
